      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Polish Workboard operations view",
        "body": "## Summary\n- polish the Workboard operations UI across card layout, filters, health metrics, details, responsive behavior, dropdowns, and tooltips\n- add guarded auto-refresh, serialized writes, linked-task reconciliation, bounded task discovery, and safer start/stop behavior\n- preserve accessible names, selected custom-select values, tooltip viewport behavior, and native-title fallback semantics\n- expand focused controller/view/tooltip/lifecycle coverage and deterministic Workboard browser E2E\n\n## Maintenance repairs\n- rebased onto current Workboard base behavior while preserving main's hide-empty-column and accessibility changes\n- deferred failed lifecycle refresh retries, preserved matching task links on enrichment failure, and committed poll results atomically so in-flight polls cannot disrupt drag-and-drop\n- hardened canonical/replacement task matching, terminal discovery cursor cycling, unresolved-start tracking, and task/session stop fallback behavior\n- kept session-only lifecycle reconciliation available when best-effort task discovery fails, while limiting unresolved task Live/Stop controls to running cards\n- retried current lifecycle reconciliation after a shared task refresh is invalidated by a concurrent card write\n- cleared obsolete task-refresh errors when refreshed cards no longer need task data, and hid dismissed floating tooltips from assistive technology\n- required linked-session abort success when a recorded task is already missing, preventing false blocked-state writeback\n- honored task-refresh backoff for session-only cards while retaining session reconciliation, and preserved cached summaries on partial full-refresh confirmation failures\n- re-armed polling across leave/re-enter teardown, cleared stopped-poll loading state, and discarded in-flight polls that overlap opening an edit draft\n- removed an unreachable same-card details toggle while keeping the modal/inert interaction model intact\n- hardened shared floating tooltip cleanup, viewport placement, accessible descriptions, and inherited native-title suppression\n- made custom-select triggers announce both their field and selected value\n- handled successful missing-task cancellations and exact task confirmations without stale lifecycle retries\n- merged current `upstream/main` and regenerated the conflicting locale metadata\n- detached stale lifecycle loads, cleared recovered dispatch refresh errors, and fully stopped in-flight polling when Workboard becomes inactive\n- marked the newly added Workboard strings as English fallbacks across all generated locale metadata until translated\n- merged current `upstream/main` again and regenerated the locale metadata conflicts against the latest Control UI strings\n\n- serialized queued forced refresh contracts so stronger diagnostics/task refresh requests cannot be silently dropped\n- preserved newer unrelated refresh errors when lifecycle task refresh later recovers\n- restored Workboard fallback markers across all generated locale metadata after current-main regeneration\n- detached invalidated Workboard load ownership so writes can immediately unblock replacement refresh and reconciliation\n\n- cleared stale cards-list errors after successful passive polling while preserving newer mutation errors, and recorded load-time task failures for lifecycle recovery\n- invalidated loaded Workboard snapshots during lifecycle teardown so reconnect or re-enable performs a fresh card load\n\n## Verification\n\nProof was run on exact pushed head `d81326b01eb84aa573a3388e5295af06ceb1d7fc` after merging current `upstream/main` `f90ec6d7bea749144222df6f09232ed3feb5db2d`.\n\n- `git merge-tree --write-tree upstream/main HEAD` - clean\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` - clean\n- focused UI and i18n suite - 8 files, 327 tests passed\n- Workboard browser E2E - 2 files, 3 tests passed\n- UI test typecheck passed\n- `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check` - all 18 locales clean with 100 tracked fallback entries per locale\n- trusted host-broker structured autoreview - clean, no accepted/actionable findings; patch correct at 0.76 confidence\n- exact-head GitHub CI completed with seven failures on paths byte-identical to current `upstream/main`; 116 checks passed, and no required checks are reported for the branch\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Workboard operations view polish, lifecycle safety, merge-conflict repair, and correct pending-translation tracking for all PR-introduced English Workboard fallback copy.\n- Real environment tested: isolated local OpenClaw PR worktree on macOS at exact pushed head `d81326b01eb84aa573a3388e5295af06ceb1d7fc`; deterministic Workboard browser E2E and focused controller/view/tooltip/lifecycle/i18n execution were used.\n- Evidence after fix: the exact PR head merges cleanly with current main; all 18 locale manifests track 100 fallback keys and pass the repository i18n check; focused UI/i18n tests, browser E2E, typechecking, and trusted structured review pass.\n- Existing visible Workboard recordings remain representative of the operations UI:\n  - writable flow recording: https://files.catbox.moe/ypr4k0.webm\n  - read-only flow recording: https://files.catbox.moe/eefb2b.webm\n  - edit/reopen persistence: https://files.catbox.moe/plruvi.png\n  - drag/status persistence: https://files.catbox.moe/lm7h10.png\n- What was not tested: no production Gateway, private card fixture, protected channel, configured binding, Crabbox/Testbox, or external live surface was mutated. Routine GitHub CI and external maintainer review were not awaited.\n",
